Change-Id: Ib9197cc9061bbba0c040f237bb52d12a60a976d7

Implement advanced MongoDB cluster actions timeout definition

Reasons:
 - cluster timeout option doesn't work properly for big deployments
   (more than 10 replicas per initial shard);
 - cluster provisioning action is unpredictable because of statement [1].

Changes:
 - implementing advanced timeout that depends on instance number;
 - applying advanced timeout definition to all cluster actions:
   - create cluster;
   - add shard;
 - implementing generic cluster action decorator that works as handler
   for successful and unsuccessful cluster modification cases, proof:
   - if cluster action is failed Taskmanager should run:
     - specific status modification method (decorator's 'callback' method);
     - specific recoverer (for cases when running additional cluster actions);

